1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 e6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Bg3 O-O 8. Bb5 Ne7?! (8... a6 { This will usually result in black walking into a classic trap.
.. } 9. Bxc6 bxc6 10. Qa4 Qc7 11. Bxd6 Qxd6 12. Qa3) 9. Bd3 b6 10. e4! { White seizes the initiative and will not stop making threats until the
position is winning } 10... dxe4 11. Nxe4 Nxe4 12. Bxe4 Rb8 13. dxc5 Bxg3 14. hxg3 (14. Qxd8 Bxf2+ 15. Kxf2 Rxd8) 14... f5 15. Qxd8 Rxd8 16. c6 Nd5 17. Bxd5 Rxd5 18. Rd1 Rxd1+ 19. Kxd1 Ba6 20. Ne5 Rc8 21. c4 b5 22. b4 bxc4 23. a4 Rd8+ 24. Kc2 Rd5 25. f4 { 1-0 (25) Carlsen,M (2840)-Bosiocic,M (2591) Doha 2016 } *


